Step 2: Install Helm (If Not Already Installed)
Before proceeding, make sure Helm is installed. If not, install Helm by running the following commands based on your operating system:
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/master/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash

3 helm create three-tier-app

4  Step 4: Modify the Helm Chart Templates
We'll modify the Helm templates for backend, frontend, and the database services.

Move the existing Kubernetes YAML files into the Helm chart:

In the three-tier-app/templates/ directory, replace the default deployment.yaml and service.yaml with your existing backend-deployment.yaml, frontend-deployment.yaml, mongo-deployment.yaml, and service files.










